#
# Dot Logging  - count life events.
#  This application based CouchApp. (http://couchapp.org/)
#

* Requirements
 - jQuery 1.5.2 (http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.5.2.min.js)
 - jQuery.mobile 1.0a4.1 (http://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.0a4.1/jquery.mobile-1.0a4.1.min.js)
 - jQuery.mobile CSS (http://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.0a4.1/jquery.mobile-1.0a4.1.min.css)
 - jqPlot 1.0.0a_r701
 - jqPlot CSS

* Dot Logging 
** install application to couchdb
1. git clone git://github.com/motokazu/Dot-Logging.git
2. cd Dot-Logging
3. couchapp push http://localhost:5984/dots
4. open browser and access to http://localhost:5984/dots/_design/dotlgng/index.html

* Dot Logging for Android
*  This application depend to libcouch-android library from https://github.com/couchone/libcouch-android.

** Build Android Application
- prepare environment
1. download eclipse from http://www.eclipse.org/ and setup.
2. setup libcouch-android. (Please reference to http://arandomurl.com/2011/02/13/developing-with-couchdb-on-android.html.)

- build application
1. open project from DotLoggingAndroid.
2. export Android application (apk).

